comments[27]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-13T21:58:35.029Z",codex-root,"Duplicate check 2026-07-13: context-engine items define relevance assembly and evaluation but no dedicated typed-graph analytics portfolio covering project planning,impact,community,and incremental temporal algorithms; this item supplies those graph primitives without duplicating ranking policy."
  "2026-07-14T09:43:36.815Z",codex-gpt5,"Implementation start 2026-07-14: deliver the first exact deterministic analytics tranche over registered relationship semantics, including execution-order and impact/knowledge signals with provenance rather than opaque scores."
  "2026-07-14T10:19:33.632Z",codex-gpt5,"Implementation evidence: added exact deterministic ordering analytics with Kahn layers, frontier, depth, topological order, critical path, and SCC cycle reporting; bounded impact with shortest explanation paths; weak/strong knowledge components, orphans, hubs; and temporal snapshot comparison. Associative relationships are excluded from execution blockers through registry precedence rather than hard-coded kind names."
  "2026-07-14T10:48:29.881Z",codex-gpt5,"PR #556 review round 1 evidence: longest-path analysis now explicitly excludes cyclic targets reached from the acyclic prefix, and temporal comparison recursively stabilizes complete edge/payload key ordering. Cycle-entry and nested payload-order regressions pass; full repository coverage is exact 100/100/100/100."
  "2026-07-14T11:06:16.985Z",codex-gpt5,"PR #556 review round 2 evidence: stable temporal keys now honor runtime objects with custom toJSON semantics before recursive key sorting. Equivalent Date and ISO payload values compare unchanged without altering native undefined omission behavior."
  "2026-07-14T11:19:54.468Z",codex-gpt5,"PR #556 review round 3 evidence: documented the deliberate source-before-target fallback as compatibility behavior for legacy and JSON-parsed relationship definitions; focused SDK tests, lint, duplicate detection, CodeFactor rules, and typecheck pass."
  "2026-07-14T11:44:56.773Z",codex-gpt5,"PR #556 review round 4 evidence: impact analysis now performs one BFS with parent-map path reconstruction instead of one shortest-path traversal per affected node. Regression coverage proves bounded and cyclic semantics and zero shortestPath calls; installed-package 10,000-node fan-out visited 10,001 nodes once in 27.28 ms. Full coverage is exact 100/100/100/100 across 5,681 tests."
  "2026-07-17T19:21:59.493Z",maintainer-agent,"Implementation progress: execution/knowledge/impact analytics are now operable from the workspace surface via pm graph analyze and pm graph impact (CLI + pm_graph MCP + PmClient.graph). analyze returns node/edge counts plus execution (acyclic, topological layers, prerequisite frontier, critical path, genuine ordering cycles) and knowledge (components, orphans, degree hubs) summaries with a shared bounded sample limit; impact returns discovery-ordered affected rows with distance and an explaining path, honoring direction/kind/depth/limit bounds and truncation metadata. Regression spec exercises both envelopes, summary suppression, and bound enforcement on a live temp workspace."
  "2026-07-17T20:19:41.275Z",maintainer-agent,"Analytics tranche verification (commit a3b47c97): detectRelationshipCommunities, findRedundantRelationshipEdges, and computeRelationshipDominators shipped with exact 100/100/100/100 coverage inside the 5,842-test full gate. Live-workspace sanity: communities converged in 5 sweeps over ~3.1k edges (149 clusters, largest 134), redundancy surfaced real blocked_by/blocks shortcut triples with witnesses, dominators over pm-usfg ranked pm-8a2s as the 91-item gate. Remaining canonical scope on this feature: incremental cached analytics only."
  "2026-07-17T21:31:25.092Z",maintainer-agent,"PR #580 MERGED (6b8ee9e4): communities/redundancy/dominators analytics are live on the public SDK and pm graph surface. Post-review upgrades: computeRelationshipDominators gained a maxDepth reachability bound with depth-truncation metadata, communities envelopes report iteration-bound non-convergence through truncated, and the redundancy/dominator index scans are Set-deduplicated. Feature stays open for incremental cached analytics only."
  "2026-07-17T23:52:43.910Z",maintainer-agent,"Implementation progress (graph-platform lane 2026-07-18): the recorded remaining scope (incremental cached analytics) shipped its first tranche — new src/sdk/graph/cache.ts WorkspaceGraphCache: SHA-256 fingerprint over every relationship-relevant item field (id/title/status/terminal-classification/parent/blocker/deps) keys reuse of the assembled workspace graph plus bounded memoization of deterministic query results (structuredClone isolation both directions, LRU eviction). runGraph and deps --format context share the cache; every pm graph envelope now carries cache {fingerprint, assembly, result} hit/miss observability. Live MCP-session proof: first audit miss/miss, repeat hit/hit, invalidation on any relationship-relevant mutation. Remaining canonical scope: true delta-incremental maintenance (label/index updates without full recompute), temporal/snapshot-comparison variants, and approximation-bounded algorithms per the AC."
  "2026-07-18T00:56:09.442Z",codex-root,"PR #581 pre-merge Greptile 5/5 robustness follow-up: canonicalized dependency entries before workspace fingerprint hashing so semantically identical dependency arrays reuse the incremental graph cache regardless of storage order. Direct regression coverage proves dependency-order invariance; 26 focused cache/orchestrator tests and strict static/docstring/package/token gates pass. The remediation non-null observation was inspected and retained because audit samples and duplicate-group keys are produced by the same deterministic formatter in one synchronous plan pass; it is a proven internal invariant, not an external unchecked input."
  "2026-07-18T01:17:22.280Z",codex-root,"PR #581 CodeRabbit exact-head follow-up: accepted review comment 3607232444 and replaced locale-sensitive localeCompare ordering at both graph-fingerprint layers with default UTF-16 sort ordering. This preserves dependency/item order independence while making the SHA-256 input deterministic across locales and operating systems. Focused cache/run tests (26) plus strict static, 100% docstring, package-boundary, and token-budget gates pass."
  "2026-07-20T03:30:16.419Z",maintainer-agent,"Continuation scope 2026-07-20: finish incremental ordering-cycle mutation advisories plus durable analytics result reuse and baseline drift reporting. Only this active analytics tranche is in progress; temporal what-if variants and the million-item evaluation matrix remain future work."
  "2026-07-20T04:04:18.967Z",maintainer-agent,"Review evidence: exact-head Greptile review 84ef563e-f412-44be-80e5-462936a5134d completed at confidence 5/5 with no actionable findings. It confirmed weak-component mutation scoping, legacy-cycle suppression, self-loop behavior, and incremental ordering-cycle advisory coverage."
  "2026-07-20T04:17:12.266Z",maintainer-agent,"Final branch evidence before PR: all 4 linked mutation/cache/history tests passed. The complete repository gate passed 318 files / 5,993 tests at exact 100/100/100/100. Temp installed-package proof exercised cross-process cache reuse and invalidation after a real mutation; component-scoped ordering-cycle warnings are covered for self-loops, legacy-cycle suppression, and cross-component isolation."
  "2026-07-20T04:53:49.812Z",maintainer-agent,"PR #622 review round 1: accepted Gemini's locale-independent advisory ordering. Cycle keys and adjacency use default UTF-16 ordering; focused mutation tests and exact repository branch coverage pass. The extension registry now also participates in workspace fingerprints, preventing stale precedence semantics in long-lived mutation/query hosts."
  "2026-07-20T05:23:27.355Z",codex-root,"Review round 2 evidence: graph filter extensibility now honors active package relationship ontologies end-to-end, preserving universal SDK customization across query/cache surfaces. Full suite passes 5,995 tests and exact 100/100/100/100; static, docstring, duplication, package-boundary, token-budget, and contract checks pass."
  "2026-07-20T05:41:23.037Z",codex-root,"PR #622 final review round: temporal analytics now retains per-type coverage drift rather than allowing cross-type aggregate cancellation; malformed per-type baseline structures are rejected. Full 5,995-test exact coverage and static gates pass."
  "2026-07-20T05:55:02.099Z",codex-root,"PR #622 durability review: cached analytics persistence is now lock-serialized across processes and query-safe on disk failures. Concurrent views retain both results; exact full coverage passes 5,996 tests."
  "2026-07-20T06:10:06.314Z",codex-gpt5,"Final delayed-review remediation evidence: durable graph envelope decoding now rejects array-shaped results maps, invalid graph maintenance/baseline flag combinations are rejected before relationship-registry resolution, fingerprinting, or graph-cache assembly, and a spy-backed regression proves no workspace cache lookup occurs. Verification: focused durable-cache suite 10/10; pnpm lint passed (ESLint, zero jscpd clones, static quality, package-boundary, token-budget, 100% docstrings); full sandboxed coverage passed 318 files / 5,996 tests at 100% statements (40,184), branches (28,240), functions (8,154), and lines (39,121)."
  "2026-07-20T06:30:15.716Z",codex-gpt5,"PR #622 latest Gemini follow-up: accepted the case-folded duplicate-row ordering concern while preserving the project's locale-independent determinism rule. Duplicate governance rows now sort holder, target, and kind by lowercase canonical value with exact-spelling tie-breakers; regressions exercise case-only holder/target/kind ties. Focused governance 19/19, ESLint/static quality, zero-clone jscpd, 100% docstrings, package-boundary/token-budget, and full 318-file / 5,996-test coverage all pass at exact 100/100/100/100 (40,191 statements; 28,240 branches; 8,155 functions; 39,126 lines)."
  "2026-07-20T06:46:51.442Z",codex-gpt5,"PR #622 review follow-up: Gemini's two AuditNodeState findings were rejected after source verification because the interface declares id and nodeStates populates id from detail.id; no runtime defect exists. Gemini/CodeRabbit's shared legacy snapshot concern was accepted for direct public-SDK callers: per-type delta reads now tolerate pre-coverage_by_type baseline/current payloads, with regressions proving zero-based positive and negative typed deltas. Full strict verification: 318 files / 5,996 tests, exact 100% statements (40,194), branches (28,242), functions (8,156), lines (39,129); lint, zero-clone, static complexity, 100% docstrings, package boundary, and token budget pass."
  "2026-07-20T06:59:07.265Z",codex-wide-sdk,"Review-loop evidence: durable audit baseline decoding now accepts the pre-coverage_by_type public snapshot shape and migrates it to an empty per-type census in memory, while still rejecting malformed present values. Full lint/static gates and 5,996-test 100% coverage gate passed."
  "2026-07-20T07:15:36.132Z",maintainer-agent,"Merged delivery evidence: PR #622 merged to main as e98282a1 with durable analytics reuse, signed per-type snapshot drift, and component-scoped incremental ordering-cycle advisories. Full 5,996-test coverage stayed exact 100/100/100/100; all final bot/check gates were green; merged-head Sentry/telemetry and Auto Release dry-run verification passed. This analytics tranche is shipped; the feature returns open for true delta maintenance, temporal what-if variants, approximation bounds, and the million-item evaluation matrix."
  "2026-07-20T07:18:50.496Z",maintainer-agent,"Post-merge delayed review disposition: Gemini comments 3612551129/3612551134 were rejected and down-voted after source verification. The shared Tarjan visitor explicitly reads absent successor rows as an empty array, and component completion uses optional chaining; the sparse induced map is intentional, allocation-efficient, and covered by a white-box regression. Both threads were answered with exact source evidence and resolved; no code change was warranted."
  "2026-07-21T03:02:58.199Z",maintainer-agent,"Duplicate-check + scope 2026-07-21: all-status review of the graph SDK confirms the current analytics surface (analyze/audit/communities/redundancy/dominators/plan + relationship-analytics.ts execution/impact/knowledge) does NOT yet implement three AC bullets: (1) order-bearing DAG *slack/float* (analyze reports critical path + prerequisite depth but no latest-start/total-float/critical-node classification); (2) impact *articulation points or bridges* + directional *fan-in/fan-out*; (3) knowledge-graph *centrality* (betweenness/closeness). A 2026-07-18 note said 'nothing else outstanding' but that under-read the AC — these are genuinely unbuilt. No parallel item exists (searched graph/centrality/slack/articulation across all statuses); this extends the canonical pm-7ob5 lineage, not a new item. This tranche ships them as new public SDK primitives (sdk/graph/scheduling.ts + sdk/graph/centrality.ts) plus thin pm graph slack/centrality/articulation subcommands, MCP + contracts + completion parity, docs, and exact-coverage tests. Temporal what-if variants and the million-item evaluation matrix (pm-m2il) remain future work."
notes[7]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-14T10:19:36.348Z",codex-gpt5,"Remaining canonical scope after this PR: dominators, community algorithms beyond exact components, redundancy detection, incremental cached analytics, and CLI/MCP projections; keep feature open."
  "2026-07-17T20:01:05.109Z",maintainer-agent,"Implementation progress (graph-query-surface lane, 2026-07-17): three of this feature's recorded remaining-scope analytics shipped as public SDK primitives in new src/sdk/graph/analytics.ts — detectRelationshipCommunities (deterministic asynchronous label propagation, sorted sweeps, lexicographic tie-break, maxIterations/minSize bounds, convergence reporting), findRedundantRelationshipEdges (transitive-reduction scan joining each directed ordering/hierarchy kind with its inverse spelling in semantic orientation, per-edge bounded BFS witness paths), computeRelationshipDominators (Cooper-Harvey-Kennedy immediate dominators over the root's reachable subgraph with per-node gating weights). Exposed as pm graph communities/redundancy/dominators + pm_graph MCP + PmClient.graph with counts-first envelopes, sample bounds, and cost metadata. Remaining canonical scope: incremental cached analytics only (dominators/communities/redundancy now shipped)."
  "2026-07-17T23:53:01.513Z",maintainer-agent,"Test-robustness finding (2026-07-18, fixed in-lane): the PR#580 communities run-spec asserted one exact partition for the seeded 5-node chain, but deterministic label propagation sweeps nodes in sorted-id order and generated ids differ per run — on a path graph two stable partitions are reachable ({5} or contiguous {3,2}), so the spec flaked (~1/5 runs). Fixed by asserting the stable invariants instead: community_count in [2,3], largest in {3,5}, clustered-membership total 7, chain-member coverage. Durable rule: LPA on path-like fixtures is sweep-order dependent; specs over generated ids must assert invariants, not one of several valid stable labelings (or use fixed-id RelationshipGraph fixtures like analytics.spec)."
  "2026-07-18T05:40:00.434Z",maintainer-agent,"PR#581 MERGED 2026-07-18: incremental cached analytics shipped — all analytics subcommands now run against the fingerprint-keyed WorkspaceGraphCache (assembly + per-query result memoization, hit/miss observability). The earlier \"remainder = incremental cached analytics only\" framing is now DONE; honest AC remainder after re-read: (a) temporal variants over immutable history — snapshot comparison, trend, change-point, counterfactual what-if (pm get --at is the substrate, pm-hib1 shipped); (b) the evaluation matrix (quality/latency/memory/update-cost/token-savings on scratch → million-item fixtures, shared with pm-m2il). Nothing else outstanding."
  "2026-07-19T04:07:32.591Z",maintainer-agent,"Incremental-analytics evidence 2026-07-19: collectNewOrderingCycleWarnings (sdk/graph/mutation-advisory.ts, shipped PR#593) assembles the FULL workspace relationship graph twice (before+after snapshots) and runs analyzeRelationshipExecution SCC analysis twice on every dep-mutating create/update (call sites create.ts ~2443, update.ts ~2887). At 1,886 nodes / 3,171 edges this is measurable per-mutation overhead and grows linearly; an incremental/cached cycle check scoped to the changed item's component is the natural consumer of this item's remainder."
  "2026-07-21T03:34:25.693Z",maintainer-agent,"Planning + structural analytics tranche shipped 2026-07-21 (branch graph-planning-structural-analytics). THREE new public SDK primitives + pm graph subcommands, filling AC bullets 1-3 that prior tranches left unbuilt: (1) analyzeRelationshipSchedule / pm graph slack — Critical Path Method over the order-bearing DAG: reuses the exact analyzeRelationshipExecution forward pass for topo order + earliest-start distances, adds the backward latest-start pass, reports total float (slack), critical classification, makespan, and excludes genuine cycles (unit task durations, deterministic, metadata-independent). (2) computeRelationshipCentrality / pm graph centrality — exact Brandes shortest-path betweenness + Wasserman-Faust closeness (single BFS sweep per source computes both) + undirected degree + directed fan-in/fan-out over the simple undirected graph. (3) findRelationshipCutStructure / pm graph articulation — iterative Tarjan low-link articulation points + bridges (single points of failure). Shared refactor: analytics.ts buildUndirectedAdjacency now delegates to a new exported forEachMatchedRelationshipEdge(edge,definition) iterator, reused by centrality (zero jscpd clones). Full wiring: enum-contracts single-source, run.ts envelopes/executors/dispatch, index.ts barrel, MCP tool-definitions, completion (bash/zsh/fish), register-list-query, tool-parameter-tables, contracts snapshot regen, docs (RELATIONSHIP_GRAPH/COMMANDS/SDK). AC REMAINDER after this tranche: structural holes (Burt constraint/brokerage), temporal what-if/trend/change-point variants over immutable history, and the million-item evaluation matrix (shared with pm-m2il)."
  "2026-07-21T04:42:31.183Z",maintainer-agent,"PR #625 MERGED 2026-07-21 (341408db) via child pm-efuo34: pm graph slack (CPM float), centrality (Brandes betweenness + Wasserman-Faust closeness + degree + precedence-oriented dependency fan-in/out), and articulation (Tarjan cut points + bridges) shipped as exact deterministic public SDK primitives. New shared helpers: orientOrderingEdge (traversal.ts), forEachMatchedRelationshipEdge (analytics.ts). AC remainder UNCHANGED: structural holes (Burt constraint/brokerage), temporal what-if/trend/change-point variants over immutable history, and the million-item evaluation matrix (pm-m2il)."
learnings[2]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-14T10:02:21.487Z",codex-gpt5,Execution analytics need an explicit precedence direction in each ordering-kind definition. An ordering boolean alone cannot distinguish source-blocks-target from source-blocked-by-target without guessing from labels.
  "2026-07-21T03:34:27.390Z",maintainer-agent,"Coverage-gate design rules for graph analytics primitives (100/100/100/100, no cheats): (a) do NOT wrap SDK calls whose kind args are pre-validated by parseKinds in try/catch rethrowGraphUsage — the catch is unreachable dead code (centrality/articulation take valid canonical kinds only; only redundancy's non-transitive-kind check is a real reachable throw). (b) Prefer Math.min/Math.max folds over gated compound conditionals (!gated || x<bound) — the compound form creates uncovered branch pairs; the fold has none. (c) A closeness map populated for EVERY source makes closeness.get(id) ?? 0 a dead ?? branch — use ! when the map is total. (d) reachableCount>0 implies distanceSum>0, so || distanceSum===0 is dead — drop it. (e) branch-coverage traps needing dedicated fixtures: multi-shortest-path predecessor append (square/4-cycle), sort id-tiebreak (parallel equal-slack chains), acyclic-node-into-cycle successor skip, self-loop ordering skip (custom allowSelf registry via new RelationshipGraph), and each --kind ternary in every executor (call once with a kind)."
